          "datePublished": "2024-07-29",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "If you analyse any school from a broader perspective there will always be some pros and many cons.\nBeing a parent of a child diagnosed with a learning disability, to me the biggest challenge was always not just acceptance but genuine concern for the growth of my child.\nAt TSVS not only did we find a school that genuinely cares about the mental well-being of our son, but also a safe space where my tears are allowed to spill, my anxiety heard and hands that hold mine to help my child get better every single day. He is included in everything; treated like an equal in his class and has classmates who love him and help him every single day. The SEN Lab at the school is one of the most emotionally equipped group of teachers led by Vinita Mam who is without a doubt the fairy godmother to my child. From the teachers, to coordinators, to aunties and the bus drivers; everyone has been briefed on how to handle a child with a learning disability and to treat it like a small inconvenient cold and not a big problem. My child is full of confidence, and is sure he will take over the world someday and for him to believe that he is capable of more than the average child is a true testament of what the school(especially his teachers - if I named them all this list would never end) have done for him.\nFor this we as parents will be; forever in your debt.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
